author: liamaflwfantasy.bsky.social
text:
1st North Melbourne
FA: Pre-FA, this list has ZERO gaps, so aim of the game will be to retain or find replacements for any retired/traded players
Draft: 2/3 yr projects to replace Kate Shierlaw and Emma Kearney, who present as the most likely players to retire in next season or two. 

#AFLW

author: liamaflwfantasy.bsky.social
text:
3rd Brisbane
FA: Half back. Brisbane have few pressing needs. If Jade Ellenger becomes more of a mid, a like-for-like potential replacement would be handy to have.  
Draft: Blessed with talents across the list, a rookie inside mid should help future proof the squad

#AFLW

author: liamaflwfantasy.bsky.social
text:
4th Adelaide
FA: Wings/Half back. If Newman leaves, her output will need replacing. Add in the need to find hb's with the capacity to exit def with pace/hands in times of need.
Draft: The Crows aren't screaming out in any one position, so an option across all 4 options to refresh the list

#AFLW

author: liamaflwfantasy.bsky.social
text:
5th Freo
FA: Keys. Brazill was excellent in def & Heatherington+Kikoak ably covered Tighe post-ACL. All have ?s about being in the side next season, so coverage may be required.
Draft: The midfield is logjammed now, but the pipeline of future inside options is running on empty

#AFLW

author: liamaflwfantasy.bsky.social
text:
6th Port
FA: Mids. The lack of a star mid with ball winning & elite use ability showed itself vs NW in the Prelim. Foley leaving also leaves a hole at half back to fill.
Draft: Medium or small forwards with the ability to replace Mules-Robinson and Lamb long term

#AFLW

author: liamaflwfantasy.bsky.social
text:
7th Richmond
FA: Half back. Sheerin move to inside mid helped their clearance game, at the cost of the speed/line-breaking capacity of their stout defensive line. 
Draft: Forwards ought to be front of mind, especially to find a long term replacement for captain Katie Brennan

#AFLW

author: liamaflwfantasy.bsky.social
text:
8th Essendon
FA: Ruck/FWD. Steph Wales injury exposed the (lack of) Dons ruck depth. With the potential to miss early 25, an Emma King-style ruck with forward skills sits atop the FA wish list
Draft: This list lacks much 'game-breaking' physicality, so physical tackle breakers are the 🎯

#AFLW
